<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I agree with mez half of the time. when we are fighting multiple purples mez is great, when a group is well balanced and fighting 2 or 3 reds, just use the AE.. its more efficient, mobs drop faster, the battle is over sooner, people who need to sit on thier butts can do so etc etc. but usually there isnt much butt sitting in these situations. I can give an example.<BR>In Keltoi I was in a group with 2 paladins, an armsman, 2 clerics, and myself all about 21-23 in the crypt pulling 2 or 3 mobs at a time. I used AE and the paladins kept the aggro with the heal chant, everything died really fast. Then a sorc joined us and wanted to mezz everything, that doubled and tripled the amount of time it took to kill a pull, which meant the spawns were slowed as well, which meant slower XP for us. So I cast AE once and the sorc yelled at me for a few minutes for doing it while the rest of the group was saying "Love that AE, it is great! No need to mezz here." She would say off color things every time I used AE, so my understanding of the situation is that the sorc was either stubborn, high-n-mighty, or just plain slow. So, that being said, Wizards need to know when to NOT use AE, and Sorcs need to know when to not waste power on mez and let the AE casters shine.
</FONT>
